AGI - New shipwreck off Lampedusa>. A 15-year-old Guinea died after the iron bark on which he traveled was overturned during rescue operations by the Coast Guard. On the other hand, fifty people were rescued, including eleven women and two minors. The 7-metre-born would have sailed, according to the first stories of the shipwrecks, at 20 on Friday from Sfax, in Tunisia.
&nbsp;
To identify the victim was the brother who, once he concluded the alleged rescue operations and landed on the Favaloro pier, began to look for it and give the alarm. The research began immediately at the point where the transhipment of migrants ended in water after the overturn of the bark on which they traveled. Despite the invitations, yelled by the military of the Captainry even with the megaphones, to stand still because they would have been transborted all, the migrants have moved all towards the side of the motorvedetta and the natante has turned over.
&nbsp;
Migrant landings in Lampedusa> continue. In 160, on board four boats, they were rescued and transhipted by the Greek-Gan patrolman of the finance guard of Taranto. The four groups were composed respectively of: 47 persons, including a minor; 39 (3 women), 50 (9 women and 4 children) and 24 16-year-old Bengali, Egyptian, Guinean, Sudanese, Senegalese, Ivorian and Malay. Three of the four said they left Sfax, paying 1,500 Tunisian dinars for the crossing on metal barks. The last 24, however, would sail from Zuara, Libya, traveling on a fiberglass boat and paying 3 thousand euros per head.
&nbsp;
"Viminale's data shows that the left is wrong while Meloni government is unequivocally able to solve even very complex problems such as immigration. If from January to March the landings in Italy are more than halved> is because the strategy of blocking departures with the involvement of the countries of origin and transit works. The results can only be further improved since after Tunisia an agreement has been reached with Albania, a dialogue has been opened with Egypt and the Mattei plan is now a reality," said Augusta Montaruli>, deputy group FdI at the House.
&nbsp;
"At last with Giorgia Meloni Europe is dealing with immigration and border control, while the scaffolder is reduced. The left that has tifato in these months against Italy comes out once again denied and defeated," he adds.
