AGI - Approximately 60 thousand faithful were present in St. Peter's Square for the celebration of Palm Sunday and the recitation of the Angelus with Pope Francis>. It makes the Vatican Gendarmerie known. The Pontiff preferred not to hold the homily>. After reading the Gospel, minutes of silence were observed for personal reflection and then directly the Creed.
&nbsp;
"I assure my prayer for the victims of the vile terrorist attack that was made last night in Moscow. The Lord welcomes them in his peace and comfort their families and converts the heart of those who "organize and implement these inhuman actions that offend God who commanded 'You will not kill'", said Pope Franceco at the end of the Angelus.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"Let us pray for all the brothers and sisters who suffer because of the war. In a special way I think of the marathon Ukraine> where so many people are without electricity because of the intense attacks against infrastructures that besides causing death and suffering entails the risk of a humanitarian catastrophe > of even larger dimensions. Please do not forget the marathon Ukraine," added Pope.&nbsp; "We think of Gaza suffering so much and many other places of war," said Bergoglio.
&nbsp;
The celebration of Palm Sunday was preceded by the tradition of commemoration of the entrance of Jesus to Jerusalem. In St. Peter's Square the olive branches were blessed and then the procession took place in the Basilica. To concelebrate with the Pontiff 30 cardinals, 25 bishops and 350 priests.&nbsp;

